<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-02T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-02T04:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/523:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-02T10:00:00+01:00">December 2, 1929—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 2—8:25 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>90. Your 77, November 30, 7 p.m.<note n="47" xml:id="d301fn47">See
                                footnote 39, <ref target="#pg_366">p. 366</ref>.</note> Italian
                            Government will communicate immediately to Moscow and Peiping in the
                            sense of your paragraph 6, telegram 73, November 26,<note n="48" xml:id="d301fn48">See footnote 16, <ref target="#pg_350">p.
                                    350</ref>.</note> with alterations as suggested in your 77,
                            November 30th and will publish its action as soon as it hears from its
                            representatives that the communications have been delivered.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>